<HEADLINE> Selleck Stars in Presidential Drama  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Actor Tom Selleck's latest role may seem out
of character for a man who once publicly supported Ronald Reagan
and the National Rifle Association.
</P>
<P>
   Television's former ''Magnum P.I.'' starred in a Sunday night
TNT special about a Democratic presidential candidate searching for
a running mate as the party's national convention is getting under
way.
</P>
<P>
   Selleck, however, insists he's been mistakenly branded as a
conservative activist.
</P>
<P>
   ''I've been a registered independent for a decade,'' he said.
''And in the last decade, I've probably given as much money to
Democrats as Republicans.''
</P>
<P>
   While promoting ''Running Mates,'' Selleck refused to endorse
either of the major candidates in the presidential race: ''I've
been asked by both candidates, but I won't do that.''
</P>
