<HEADLINE> Inner City Ministry earns HUD award for ''Best Practice''  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   SCHENECTADY, N.Y. (AP) - Federal housing secretary Andrew Cuomo
awarded the Schenectady Inner City Ministry the ''Best of the
Best'' Best Practices designation.
</P>
<P>
   The designation describes a Housing and Urban Development-funded
program that uses innovative methods to help people in the
community it serves.
</P>
<P>
   ''Many local governments and groups are successfully using HUD
assistance for innovative programs to revitalize communities and
bring new opportunities to American families,'' Cuomo said. ''By
recognizing these success stories, which we call best practices, we
will help communities across the nation learn from each other.''
</P>
<P>
   SICM is a partnership of 53 congregations working on human
services, including running the emergency food pantry and helping
people infected with HIV and AIDS.
</P>
</TEXT>
