<HEADLINE> Dole Salutes WWII Veterans  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SPRINGFIELD, Ill. (AP) -- Bob Dole led the Illinois State Fair
crowd in a chorus of ''Happy Birthday'' for a fellow veteran who
got an unexpected present -- medals for his World War II service.
</P>
<P>
   ''I was surprised,'' said an obviously pleased Thomas Ryder, 81,
of Sunday's ceremony. ''I knew nothing about this deal.''
</P>
<P>
   Dole, who was badly wounded in World War II, also received a
check for $987,000 -- the state's contribution to a national World
War II memorial in Washington.
</P>
<P>
   Ryder received good conduct, victory and campaign medals. Four
other veterans also collected medals they never received after
their tours of duty.
</P>
<P>
   Often, medals weren't awarded because soldiers didn't take the
time to fill out the required paperwork at the war's conclusion.
</P>
</TEXT>
