<HEADLINE> Dow Gains 104; Nasdaq Adds 43  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks rose Monday, as cautious investors tried
to reconcile positive economic news with fears of a second-half
earnings slowdown.
</P>
<P>
   In mid-afternoon trading on Wall Street, the Dow Jones
industrial average was up 104.03 at 11,131.83.
</P>
<P>
   Broader stock indicators were higher.
</P>
<P>
   The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index was up 14.28 at 1,486.12, and
the Nasdaq composite index was up 42.73 at 3,832.20.
</P>
<P>
   Retail stocks helped lift the Dow index. Home Depot shares rose
$2.50 to $58.438, and Wal-Mart Stores was up 93.75 cents at $52.50.
</P>
<P>
   Semiconductor shares also surged after an analyst said chip
prices should rise as demand increases later in the year. Micron
Technology rose $4.063 to $79.813, and Advanced Micro Devices rose
$4.50 to $61.50.
</P>
<P>
   Telecommunications parts maker Ciena Corp., up $6.75 to
$162.875, helped the Nasdaq.
</P>
<P>
   Blue-chip stocks rose last week on encouraging inflation data,
including a Labor Department report that showed that wholesale
prices remained virtually the same in July after a huge jump in
June caused by soaring energy costs. The Dow index closed above
11,000 Friday for the first time since April 25.
</P>
<P>
   Investors have kept pressure on technology stocks, however, in
the wake of warnings from some widely held companies that earnings
could fall in the second half of 2000.
</P>
<P>
   Those conflicting dynamics have left investors with no clear
motivation to either buy or sell stocks. The result has been that
stocks have mostly fluctuated from day to day without breaking out
in any one direction.
</P>
<P>
   ''The market is in the midst of tentative trading. On balance,
this is a market attempting to find a footing,'' said Alan
Ackerman, chief investment strategist Fahnestock Inc. in New York.
</P>
<P>
   ''We're basically on hold until the Federal Reserve Board
meeting on Aug. 22,'' he added. ''Investors are watching and
waiting. We need to work our way through the uncertainty of what
the Fed will do.''
</P>
<P>
   Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 5-to-4 margin on the
New York Stock Exchange, where volume came to 605.84 million
shares, down from Friday's pace.
</P>
<P>
   The Russell 2000 index was up 3.28 at 513.55.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
