<HEADLINE> Woman tells police she was robbed by man wearing 'Goofy' costume  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NEW YORK (AP) - A Bronx woman claims she was robbed early Monday
morning in her home by two men, one wearing a Goofy costume and
another man possibly dressed like the Grinch, police said.
</P>
<P>
   The 58-year-old woman, whose identity was not released, said she
was asleep in her home in the Spencer Estates neighborhood -
described by police as a quiet and nice residential area near
Pelham Bay Park - when she awoke shortly before 3 a.m. to find the
two men in her room.
</P>
<P>
   The woman described one man as wearing a full Goofy costume, and
the other dressed as a ''green, furry creature.'' Police speculate
that the woman may have been referring to the Grinch character from
the Dr. Seuss books, but were not certain. Goofy, a Disney
character, has long, floppy ears and wears a hat.
</P>
<P>
   The woman said the men pointed guns at her and stole $600 in
cash, some jewelry, a TV set and her car. The suspects remained at
large Monday. Police were not certain how the men got into the
woman's house.
</P>
<P>
   Police were investigating whether the robbery was connected to
the burglary of the woman's next door neighbor on Aug. 6, when
$25,000 in cash was taken. The owner of that home was asleep at the
time the money - in a briefcase - was taken.
</P>
<P>
   -
</P>
<P>
   Crime scene: 3279 Spencer Drive, Bronx.
</P>
