<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-14 16:32 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Driver being followed by police crashes, dies  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   HAMBURG, N.Y. (AP) - A driver who was being followed by police
for allegedly driving recklessly was killed when his car collided
with a pickup truck.
</P>
<P>
   Richard Sanford, 28, of Buffalo was pronounced dead at the scene
of the 12:36 p.m. crash Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   The driver of the truck, Richard Klopp, 44, of Derby was treated
for minor injuries at Erie County Medical Center and released. His
passengers, three children also were treated for minor injuries.
</P>
<P>
   Town of Hamburg police said the incident began when the Evans
Police Department received a call about a vehicle operating
recklessly. Evans officers, with emergency lights and sirens
operating, spotted and followed the car into Hamburg in an attempt
to stop it, Hamburg police said.
</P>
<P>
   The Sanford vehicle crossed double yellow lines and into the
path of the Klopp vehicle. The collision, which occurred on a
stretch of Route 5 where the speed limit is 55 mph, forced both
vehicles off the roadway and into woods.
</P>
<P>
   Police said Monday it was unclear how fast the Sanford vehicle
was traveling when it crashed.
</P>
</TEXT>
