<HEADLINE> Schumer takes a tumble off his bike  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   LOS ANGELES (AP) - U.S. Sen. Charles Schumer wanted to fit in a
bike ride in the California sunshine and he almost paid dearly for
it.
</P>
<P>
   The New Yorker attending the Democratic National Convention took
a tumble Sunday after colliding with a car. Schumer was left with
some bruises on his shin and a bit of limp after landing on his
hip.
</P>
<P>
   ''I'm fine - sore but fine,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Schumer said the lobbyist who hit him recognized him and
panicked that he had injured a U.S. senator.
</P>
<P>
   ''He was very, very worried but it was all my fault. No
lawsuit,'' Schumer said.
</P>
<P>
   Schumer, an avid biker, had rented ''a nice little mountain bike
for $14 a day'' and was testing out the gears as he pulled out of a
hotel driveway. The car was pulling into the hotel and he didn't
see it until he was nearly on top of it. Schumer hit the brakes,
then hit the car.
</P>
<P>
   The accident didn't stop Schumer from taking a 20-mile ride
along Benedict Canyon. He said he intends to take another bike ride
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Still, Schumer joked that the incident just goes to show that
New Yorkers should not venture into car-crazy Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
   ''This is not a safe city like New York. This would not have
happened in Brooklyn,'' he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
