<HEADLINE> Stormy Jack Wins Good Deal Stakes  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DEL MAR, Calif. (AP) -- Stormy Jack overtook 11-10 favorite
Gibson County in the final yards in a battle of Bob Baffert-trained
3-year-olds to win Monday's $106,200 Real Good Deal Stakes at Del
Mar by one length.
</P>
<P>
   Ridden by Victor Espinoza, Stormy Jack covered seven furlongs in
1:21 3-5 and, as the 2-1 second-favorite, paid $6.20, $2.80 and
$2.10.
</P>
<P>
   The victory, worth $63,720, was the second straight at the
current Del Mar meeting and fourth in nine starts overall for
Stormy Jack. It raised the career earnings of the California-bred
son of Bertrando to $300,610.
</P>
<P>
   Gibson County, ridden by David Flores, crossed the finish line
eight lengths in front of Echo Eddie and returned $2.80 and $2.10.
</P>
<P>
   Echo Eddie, ridden by Iggi Puglisi, was three-quarters of a
length ahead of Royal Irish at the wire and paid $2.20 to show.
</P>
<P>
   Each of the five entries carried 121 pounds except fifth-place
finisher Know Sumthin, who carried 114.
</P>
<P>
   Ceeband and Immense Variety were scratched.
</P>
</TEXT>
