<HEADLINE> Blackhawks' McCabe Wins Arbitration  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CHICAGO (AP) -- Defenseman Bryan McCabe won his arbitration case
against the Chicago Blackhawks on Monday and will receive $2.15
million next season.
</P>
<P>
   McCabe, acquired in a 1999 trade with the Vancouver Canucks, had
six goals and 19 assists and 139 penalty minutes in 79 games last
season.
</P>
<P>
   The 25-year-old McCabe, who was a restricted free agent, filed
for arbitration after the Blackhawks declined to pick up their
option on the final year of his contract.
</P>
<P>
   The Blackhawks said that a ruling in their arbitration case with
defenseman Anders Eriksson is expected on Tuesday.
</P>
</TEXT>
