<HEADLINE> Smolinski OKs Kings 1-Year Contract  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Bryan Smolinski agreed to a one-year contract
with the Los Angeles Kings on Monday, which canceled an arbitration
hearing scheduled for Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   ''We are happy to get this deal done with Bryan,'' Kings general
manager Dave Taylor said. ''His play last season solidified our
second line and we look forward to Bryan having a successful
season.''
</P>
<P>
   The 28-year-old center, who was a restricted free agent, had 20
goals and 36 assists in 79 games last season. He was acquired from
the New York Islanders prior to the start of the season.
</P>
<P>
   He has scored at least 20 goals in four of his eight NHL
seasons.
</P>
<P>
   The former Michigan State star was scoreless in four playoff
games last spring, his first postseason action since he played for
the Pittsburgh Penguins in 1996.
</P>
