<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brewers Place Jose Hernandez on DL  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MILWAUKEE (AP) -- The Milwaukee Brewers placed infielder Jose
Hernandez on the 15-day disabled list, retroactive to Aug. 11, on
Monday night.
</P>
<P>
   Hernandez, who signed a three-year, $10 million free-agent
contract to be Milwaukee's everyday third baseman, is hitting .247
with 11 homers and 53 RBIs while striking out a team-high 110
times. He hit safely in five of the last six games he played.
</P>
<P>
   He was scratched from the Brewers' lineup on Friday when he was
seized with back spasms that made it nearly impossible for him to
walk. Hernandez, who saw a chiropractor over the weekend and was
prescribed rest, was seen on crutches in the Brewers' clubhouse.
</P>
<P>
   Milwaukee recalled infielder Mark Sweeney from Triple-A
Indianapolis to replace Hernandez. Sweeney, who hit .217 in 39
games with the Brewers this year, is hitting .509 (28-for-55) with
14 RBIs in 18 games for Indianapolis.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
